<HEAD>Liquid Gas Tanker Explodes, 7 Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Seven people were killed when a tanker
truck carrying liquified natural gas collided with a pickup truck on
Margarita Island, a local resort off eastern Venezuela, authorities
said.
   The accident Thursday burned to death the pickup driver, his wife
and 9-year-old niece. The tanker, rocketed in the air by the blast,
crushed three pedestrians to death as it fell, and the driver later
died of burns at a local hospital, police and doctors said.
   Forty other people, including 12 children, suffered burns. Twenty
of the most seriously injured were transferred by military plane 210
miles southwest to Caracas for treatment.
   The tank truck belonged to the state oil company Corporven, an
affiliate of Petroleos de Venezuela.
</TEXT>
