<HEAD>Party Sources Say Parliament President Has Resigned</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The president of West Germany's
parliament resigned today after coming under fire for a
Kristallnacht anniversary speech that called the Hitler rule
``glorious'' in the view of many Germans, party sources said.
</TEXT>
