<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     11-11 0413</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0424</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cold Front Whips Through Rockies</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   One cold front swept off the East Coast early today while another
raced through the Rockies, bringing snow to the Colorado mountains
and western Wyoming as it spread into the northern Plains.
   Four to 8 inches of snow was expected in some areas.
   Early this morning, rain fell on northern Maine, coastal sections
of Massachusetts and North Carolina. Patchy showers were reported
along the Gulf Coast.
   Some rain and snow also extended from the northern Rockies to
eastern Washington. A few showers were reported in the southwestern
states.
   Today's forecast called for snow from the central Rockies into
the northern Plains; rain and thunderstorms through the central
Plains, Oklahoma and central Texas; light snow showers scattered
through northern New England and along the southern shores of the
lower Great Lakes; widespread rain through the Pacific Northwest;
and sunny skies for much of the Ohio Valley and eastern states.
   High temperatures were forecast to be in the 30s from northeast
Minnesota to northern parts of the upper Great Lakes, much of
Wyoming and South Dakota; in the 40s from the Pacific Northwest
across much of the northern and central Rockies, the northern and
central Plains, the upper half of the Mississippi Valley, the Ohio
Valley and lower Great Lakes to northern New England; in the 70s and
80s in Florida, the Gulf Coast region, southern Texas, southern New
Mexico and the desert Southwest; and in the 50s and 60s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 20
degrees at Jamestown, N.D., to 76 degrees at Corpus Christi Naval
Air Station, Texas, and Palacios, Texas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 48 fair; Boston 50 fair; Buffalo 41 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C. 67 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 36 cloudy; Cleveland
42 showery; Detroit 38 cloudy; Miami 70 fair; New York 49 fair;
Philadelphia 46 fair; Pittsburgh 38 fair; Portland, Maine 47 fair;
Washington 54 wind.
   _Central: Bismarck 26 fair; Chicago 36 partly cloudy; Dallas-Fort
Worth 50 partly cloudy; Denver 32 cloudy; Des Moines 23 fair;
Indianapolis 34 cloudy; Kansas City 34 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 31
cloudy; Nashville 44 fair; New Orleans 67 cloudy; St. Louis 34 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 44 partly cloudy; Anchorage 25 fair; Las Vegas
56 fair; Los Angeles 61 partly cloudy; Phoenix 68 cloudy; Salt Lake
City 42 showery; San Diego 61 drizzle; San Francisco 54 fair;
Seattle 42 partly cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 39 fair; Toronto 39 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
