<HEAD>Text Of Jenninger's Resignation Speech</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Kristallnacht</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the text of Philipp Jenninger's
resignation announcement as provided by Jenninger's office. The text
was translated by The Associated Press.
   ``The reactions to my speech yesterday to the German parliament
have deeply shocked me and have greatly depressed me.
   ``My speech was not understood by many listeners the way I had
intended it to be. I am deeply sorry and I am very hurt, if I have
offended the feelings of others.
   ``During my whole political career _ most recently as president
of the German parliament _ I have been active in working for
reconciliation with the Jews and for the vital interests of the
state of Israel.
   ``I always have been an uncompromising foe of every type of
totalitarian rule, not least because of the experiences of my
parents under the Nazi regime, who were opposed to the dictatorship
and as a result had to accept disadvantages.''
   ``It is important that the office of the Bundestag president not
be damaged. I must assume that many of my colleagues no longer have
the necessary confidence in my leadership. For this reason I
announce my resignation from the office of Bundestag president.''
</TEXT>
