<TEXT>
   An official of the Israeli-allied South
Lebanon Army escaped assassination when a bomb exploded near his
car, a statement from the militia said today.
   Beirut newspapers published the statement, which said the charge
went off Thursday as Alameddine Badawi and his bodyguard drove
through the western entrance to southern Hasbaya village.
   The men escaped unharmed but their car was damaged, the statement
said.
