<HEAD>Afghan Rebel Leader Says POW Talks With Soviets To Begin Soon</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PETER JAMES SPIELMANN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>UNITED NATIONS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Afghan guerrilla leaders will soon begin
talks with the Soviet Union on the exchange of prisoners of war from
the 9-year-old conflict in Afghanistan, a rebel leader said.
   ``We would like to have direct talks with the Russians at the
highest level ... to talk about all the issues except one, the
formation of our future government,'' said Burhanuddin Rabbani,
leader of a seven-party guerrilla alliance.
   ``We could talk about other issues, including the war prisoners.
There was a statement by the Russian Embassy in Islamabad that they
