Geneva by Afghanistan, Pakistan, the United States and the Soviet
Union, Moscow began withdrawing its more than 100,000 troops from
Afghanistan on May 15th.
   Half the troops were out by Aug. 15, and the accords call for the
remainer to be removed by Feb. 15.
