<HEAD>Commerce Secretary Will Leave with Reagan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Commerce Secretary C. William Verity said today
he will not seek reappointment when George Bush becomes president
Jan. 20.
   ``He wants younger people and I applaud him for that,'' said
Verity, who is 71. ``I was retired when I took this job, and I guess
