<HEAD>Bomb Explodes at Ruling Party's Building</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANKARA, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb exploded at a building of the ruling
Motherland Party, causing panic in the neighborhood but no injuries,
a party official said Friday.
   The bomb went off late Thursday night on a first-floor balcony of
the building, which was empty at the time, said Ali Turkyasar, the
head of the party's Mamak district in Ankara.
   The blast shattered some of the building's windows and caused
panic among residents of the neighborhood, Turkyasar said.
   Police were investigating.
