<1ST_LINE>r i AM-NaziSlogans     11-11 0178</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Nazi Slogans,0182</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pro-Nazi Slogans Appear During Visit By Jewish Group</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Crystal Night, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WESEL, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pro-Nazi slogans appeared on the walls
of two schools and a museum during a visit to a small town by a
group of Jewish former residents, town officials said Friday.
   ``Auschwitz was too small,'' said one slogan, referring to the
infamous Nazi death camp. ``That's the way to the gas chamber,''
said another sign, according to city officials in Wesel.
   The signs appeared in the nearby town of Xanten, said the
officials, who spoke on condition of anonymity. Wesel and Xanten are
about 25 miles northwest of Duesseldorf.
   The group consisted of 16 Jews from the United States, Israel,
England and the Netherlands. They fled from the Wesel and Xanten
area after the Nazis came to power in 1933, the officials said.
   The visit was planned to coincide with ceremonies marking the
50th anniversary of Kristallnacht, the first organized Nazi pogrom
against Jews.
   The mayors of Wesel and Xanten apologized to the group, which
left Wesel Friday.
</TEXT>
