<HEAD>Brother-in-Law of President Killed</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   PORT-AU-PRINCE, Haiti (AP) _ Police on Friday found the
bullet-riddled body of President Prosper Avril's brother-in-law
inside a car, Radio Soleil reported.
   The Roman Catholic-run station said the body was indentified as
Louis-Marie Bonnet, an immigration department supervisor who worked
at the airport.
   Bonnet, 28, was married to the younger sister of Marie-Ange
Avril, the president's wife. The sister's name was not available.
   Witnesses told the radio they heard gunshots Thursday night but
were too frightened to come out. The body was found at 9:30 a.m.
Friday.
   Airport workers described Bonnet as efficient and honest.
   Avril came to power in a Sept. 17 coup led by rank-and-file
soldiers demanding democratic reforms. Avril replaced Lt. Gen. Henri
Namphy.
   Namphy came to power in February 1986 after Jean-Claude Duvalier
fled into exile in France.
