<HEAD>Three Presumed Dead in Navy Helicopter Crash in Arabian Sea</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Navy anti-submarine helicopter crashed while
preparing to land on a frigate in the North Arabian Sea and its
three crewmen were presumed dead, officials announced Friday.
   The SH-2F helicopter was returning to the USS Barbey at the end
of a dawn flight and crashed on approach, said Ken Mitchell,
