<HEAD>Unidentified Man Jumps White House Fence, Is Arrested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man climbed the White House fence Friday
evening but was immediately apprehended without incident, the Secret
Service said.
   Bill Corbett, spokesman for the service, said the unarmed man
climbed the 8-foot fence on the White House's north side at about
6:15 p.m., but did not verbally or physically threaten anyone.
   Corbett said the man's identity will not be released until
Saturday, when a federal magistrate decides if the intruder should
be charged or if he should be held for observation.
