<HEAD>London Shares Down</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New thruout with closing figures.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed sharply lower in heavy trading
Friday on the London Stock Exchange as the dollar continued its
recent slide.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 23.5
points, or 1.3 percent, to 1,802.7. The Financial Times 30-share
index dropped 17.6 points to 1,461.2 and the Financial Times 500
share index fell 12.64 to 1,028.63.
   Volume was a heavy 705.8 million shares, well up from 586.7
million shares a day earlier.
   The market remained preoccupied throughout the session by the
dollar's renewed weakness, dealers said.
