<HEAD>Shearson Agress to Settle </HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc. has agreed to pay
$7.4 million to the Federal Savings and Loan Insurance Corp. in
settlement of a claim that a former Shearson employee caused losses
at Home Federal Savings and Loan Association in Ponce, Puerto Rico.
   The FSLIC announced late Thursday that the brokerage firm settled
a civil suit alleging that Miguel Serrano, a former employee of a
Shearson subsidiary in Puerto Rico that has since closed, caused the
S&L to lose money in a series of transactions involving the
placement of brokered deposits.
   Shearson had contended that Serrano's actions were outside the
scope of his employment.
